<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Sharon Osbourne said she quarantined from her CBS panel show The Talk Monday after her three-year-old granddaughter Minnie tested positive for COVID-19.</p>

<p>'I was meant to be in the studio, I was so looking forward to it,' Osbourne, 67, said on the show. 'And then, unfortunately, one of my granddaughters has come down with Covid. She's okay; she's doing good. I don't have it.'</p>

<p>Osbourne told her fellow panelists that her relatives were in good health amid the family scare, including her son (and Minnie's father) Jack, who is living with multiple sclerosis.</p>

<p>The latest: Sharon Osbourne, 67, said she quarantined from her CBS panel show The Talk Monday after her three-year-old granddaughter Minnie tested positive for COVID-19</p>

<p>'Her daddy doesn't have it. Her mommy doesn't have it. Her sisters don't. She got it from somebody who works for my son. And it just goes to show you, she's three years of age, that children can get Covid.'</p>

<p>Osbourne said her heart was with the show on it's 11th season debut, but she was acting out of caution amid the pandemic, and following safety protocols.</p>

<p>'Oh my Lord, I want to see you guys so bad,' she said. 'I've got one more week left of quarantining and then I'm out.</p>

<p>'And as I say, I don't have it. I keep testing negative, but, you know, you have to be safe.'</p>

<p>Update: Osbourne told her fellow panelists that her relatives were in good health amid the family scare, including her son (and Minnie's father) Jack, who is living with multiple sclerosis</p>

